Quantum CSV Grid / Columnar Runtime Constitution

This file is a self-contained single-file data runtime.
Single HTML is the product boundary.

Core Identity:
- CDN / Babel / React / MUI are the dynamic runtime foundation.
- Worker owns heavy CSV, OPFS, columnar storage, query, pivot, time, graph execution, Observation Engine v1, HyperTensor Adaptive Kernel v2, Hybrid Surface Bus, and Distributed Execution Plane.
- App owns orchestration, state projection, and user interaction.
- UI is projection; heavy domain logic must stay in Worker-side runtime domains.
- Storage is columnar cache, not raw CSV preservation.

Runtime Principles:
- Keep boot light, observable, and recoverable.
- Keep the single-file form; do not convert to npm/build structure by default.
- Heavy processing must stay off the UI thread.
- Storage-backed datasets must be validated before use.
- Destructive storage cleanup requires explicit confirmation.
- Runtime code and diagnostics are the source of truth.

Ownership Rules:
- CSV owns streaming, parsing, cleaning, and schema inference.
- Storage owns OPFS, manifests, chunks, integrity, repair, external sync, and cleanup.
- Query owns predicates, pushdown, Observation Plan, bitset evaluation, chunk execution, sorting, and worker-pool execution.
- Analytics owns search, data query, pivot, and time series.
- Graph owns graph query planning, execution, result windows, graph search, graph pivot, and graph time.
- App connects domains but should not become domain logic.

Volume Map:
- Total: about 10.8k lines.
- Worker: about 4.5k lines.
- React App: about 6.1k lines.
- Bootstrap: small CDN/Babel/module loader.

Change Rule:
Observe -> Plan -> Do -> Check -> Act -> Lock.

Keep this block short.
Update only when runtime identity, ownership, boot policy,
storage boundary, query boundary, or graph boundary changes.
-->

